Former Aviation minister, Femi Fani-Kayode, has said he has not left the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), denying statements credited to the All Progressives Congress (APC) that he has decamped to the party.
Fani-Kayode, in a tweet on his verified Twitter handle Femi @realFFK, said: “Though, we have had meetings across party lines and we are in a season of political consultations, I have not left the PDP.”
